# Placement Portal Application - Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A **full-stack Placement Portal** with Flask + Vue.js 3 + SQLite + Redis + Celery supporting three roles: Admin, Company, and Student.

## Project Structure

```
sujith/
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py              # Flask app factory, serves frontend
│   ├── config.py           # Configuration (DB, Redis, Mail, JWT)
│   ├── models.py           # 6 SQLAlchemy models
│   ├── tasks.py            # 3 Celery tasks (daily, monthly, CSV)
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   └── routes/
│       ├── auth.py         # Login, register, /me
│       ├── admin.py        # Full CRUD + reports
│       ├── company.py      # Profile, drives, applications, interviews
│       └── student.py      # Profile, drives, apply, history, export
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html          # Entry point (CDN: Vue 3, Bootstrap 5, Chart.js)
    └── static/
        ├── css/style.css   # Custom design system
        └── js/
            ├── app.js      # Vue Router + auth state
            └── components/ # 17 Vue components
```

## How to Run

```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
# Open http://localhost:5000
```

**Admin credentials:** `admin@ppa.com` / `admin123`

For Celery/Redis (optional for async jobs):
```bash
redis-server
celery -A tasks.celery_app worker --loglevel=info
celery -A tasks.celery_app beat --loglevel=info
```

